This paper deals with unsupervised text style transfer, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new model for controlling multiple attributes in textual data, which involves learning a latent representation. This aspect of the paper makes it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. The paper also mentions the use of domain adversarial training, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing. Finally, the paper proposes a new mechanism based on back-translation, which is a technique used in neural machine translation (cs.NE).
